Sentencas: Metal supported solid oxide fuel cell (MSC) technology has a significant potential for mobile applications, due to high electrical efficiencies, fuel flexibility, cheap materials, and mechanical robustness.
Titulo: Metal Supported SOFCs for Mobile Applications using Hydrocarbon Fuels

Sentencas: The MSC concept in the current study relies on scalable, ceramic processing methodology.
Titulo: Metal Supported SOFCs for Mobile Applications using Hydrocarbon Fuels

Sentencas: Two MSC generations with different anodes, one with a FeCr-ScYSZ-based anode backbone and one with a FeCr-titanate based anode backbone, both infiltrated with GDC and Ni electro catalysts, were tested using methane containing fuel.
Titulo: Metal Supported SOFCs for Mobile Applications using Hydrocarbon Fuels

Sentencas: It was found that the internal reforming activity of the anodes is reduced as compared to state-of-the-art Ni-cermet anodes, due to the lower Ni content in the anodes of the MSCs.
Titulo: Metal Supported SOFCs for Mobile Applications using Hydrocarbon Fuels
Metal Supported SOFCs for Mobile Applications using Hydrocarbon Fuels

Sentencas: 0.22 W cm(-2) were obtained at 650 degrees C in a methane/steam fuel and long-term tests at medium to high fuel utilization were successfully demonstrated on the titanate based MSC.
Titulo: Metal Supported SOFCs for Mobile Applications using Hydrocarbon Fuels
